## 🏗️ Inventory System — Major Upgrade

### Core Principles
- Inventory is **location-specific** — employees must be clocked in at a location to update it
- **System categories are locked**: Produce, Meat, Seafood, Dairy, Dry Goods, Liquor, Beer, Wine, Non-Alcoholic, Cleaning, Paper/Supplies, Other
- Duplicate items: merge silently — admin cleans up later
- Backorders: update only quantity received; low stock alerts stay active for unreceived items
- Currency from `locations.currency_symbol` — never hardcoded

---

### Phase 1 — Database Migration ✅
- [x] `suppliers` table — name, contact, phone, email, payment_terms, default_tax
- [x] `inventory_items` table — owner-scoped; locked category CHECK; par_level, par_reset_on_sod
- [x] `location_inventory` table — per-location quantities; unique on `(location_id, inventory_item_id)`
- [x] `invoices` table — supplier_id, invoice_number, date, status (paid/unpaid), financials, raw_ocr_text
- [x] `invoice_line_items` table — invoice_id, inventory_item_id, name, size, qty, unit_price, extended_price, received (backorder flag)
- [x] `inventory_transfers` table — from/to location, item, quantity, transferred_by
- [x] RLS policies — owner-only access on all new tables
- [x] Supabase Storage bucket `order-scans` — RLS: owner reads/writes own files

### Phase 2 — Invoice / Packing Slip Scanner (App) ✅
- [x] `OrderScannerScreen.tsx` — camera UI, base64 image capture, clock-in gate enforced
  - Import path: `../../lib/supabase`; uses direct `supabase` import (AsyncStorage pattern)
- [x] `api/inventory/scan-order.ts` — Next.js API endpoint
  - Auth via `getUserFromRequest`; clock-in check via `time_entries`
  - Google Vision OCR → Claude Sonnet parses → locked category list
  - Returns `{ success, rawText, parsed }` to app
  - Env vars: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `GOOGLE_VISION_API_KEY`

### Phase 3 — Supplier Management (Website Dashboard) ✅
- [x] `DashboardInventory.tsx` — complete new component, 4-tab interface
  - **📦 Items** — inventory list, qty vs par_level, low stock badges, add/edit/delete, category filter
  - **🧾 Invoices** — all invoices across suppliers, expandable line items, backorder indicators, mark paid/unpaid, summary cards
  - **🏭 Suppliers** — list → detail view, invoice history, total spend, unpaid balance, add/edit/delete
  - **🔄 Transfers** — log location-to-location transfers, view transfer history
  - Currency always from `locations.currency_symbol`; toast notifications throughout

### Phase 4 — Par Levels & Start of Day Integration ✅ (partial)
- [x] `fetchInventoryParSnapshot()` in `reports.ts` — queries `inventory_items` + `location_inventory`
- [x] `InventoryParSnapshot` / `InventoryParItem` types exported from `reports.ts`
- [x] `generateDailyReport()` — attaches `inventorySnapshot` to EoD report; below-par items sorted first
- [x] EoD detail modal in `ReportsScreen.tsx` — inventory snapshot section in report view
- [ ] `StartOfDayReportScreen.tsx` — add inventory section; "Add to order list" button per flagged item
- [ ] `DashboardOverview.tsx` — low stock alert card using `location_inventory` + `par_level`
- [ ] Stamp `last_checked_at` on `par_reset_on_sod = true` items when SoD generated

### Phase 5 — Dashboard Analytics — Inventory 🔲
